---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<Base
  title="04 · For the Chaperone — Interphase"
  current="04 · Chaperone"
  prev={{ href: `${base}/03-product`, num: '03', title: 'Product & Prototype' }}
  next={{ href: `${base}/05-organisation`, num: '05', title: 'The Adoption Moat' }}
>
  <!-- COVER -->
  <section class="cover">
    <div class="shell">
      <p class="eyebrow cover-eyebrow">04 · For the practitioner</p>
      <h1>You have been<br />working without<br /><em>the signal layer</em><br />you always needed.</h1>
      <p class="cover-sub">
        Interphase is a platform built for senior practitioners — coaches, OD
        consultants, change managers — who have spent their careers working
        in high-stakes transformations with surveys, interviews, and intuition.
        This is what it gives you.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT YOU'VE BEEN WORKING WITHOUT -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">The problem you already know</p>
        <h2>Walking into<br />high-stakes terrain,<br /><em>half-blind.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p class="lead">You know the feeling. A client enters transformation. You arrive with the tools of your profession — interviews, pulse surveys, stakeholder maps, informal conversations — and within a week you are navigating the real work with a fraction of the information you need.</p>

          <p>Surveys lie. Or rather, they tell you what people are willing to say publicly about their experience of change. Interviews are time-sampled and status-contaminated. Observation is expensive and invasive. And even when everything is done well, weeks pass between touchpoints and the organisation shifts invisibly in the gaps.</p>

          <p>You compensate — because you are good at what you do. You pattern-match. You read rooms. You develop hypotheses and test them in the next conversation. But there is a signal layer that would make every part of this sharper, and until now it has not existed.</p>

          <div class="compare">
            <div class="compare-col">
              <h3>What you have now</h3>
              <div class="compare-item">Pulse surveys and interviews — both subject to social desirability bias</div>
              <div class="compare-item">No continuous signal between engagements — the organisation shifts invisibly between your visits</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Intervention timing driven by the project calendar, not by readiness</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Junior consulting time spent on data gathering rather than interpretation</div>
              <div class="compare-item">No longitudinal view of how individual capacity develops over time</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Outcomes are hard to attribute — what moved the needle?</div>
            </div>
            <div class="compare-col us">
              <h3>What Interphase gives you</h3>
              <div class="compare-item">Continuous, privately-generated reflection data — honest because it is structurally protected from social consequence</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Real-time signal between engagements — the dashboard updates as things shift</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Intervention triggered by readiness, not by the calendar</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Data gathering fully automated — your time goes to interpretation and human contact</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Longitudinal view of how reflective capacity develops across weeks and transformation phases</div>
              <div class="compare-item">Attribution is visible: signal before and after each intervention</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT YOU SEE -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">The data lens</p>
        <h2>What you <em>actually see.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p class="lead">You never see individual reflections. You do not want to, and the architecture does not allow it. What you see is the aggregate — patterns that only exist because enough people have contributed that individual attribution is impossible.</p>

          <p>This is not a constraint on your work. It is what makes your work trustworthy in the first place. The moment anyone on the employee side suspects that their words could reach you personally, the data collapses into performance. Your entire value as a practitioner depends on their trust that the platform will not betray them — and the architecture guarantees it in a way that policy never could.</p>

          <div class="rows">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">L1</div>
              <div class="row-label">Private<strong>Individual reflection</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Not accessible to you</h4>
                <p>Complete reflection content belongs entirely to the individual. Not to you, not to leadership, not to Interphase. This is the layer that produces the honesty that makes everything above it valuable.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">L2</div>
              <div class="row-label">Your layer<strong>Aggregate signal</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>The patterns you interpret</h4>
                <p>Where capacity is accumulating. Where it is stuck. Which questions are surfacing repeatedly across a team. Participation patterns and gaps. Reflective depth trends over time. Visible only above the participation threshold — if too few people in a unit have contributed, no signal is shown.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">L3</div>
              <div class="row-label">Your output<strong>Leadership guidance</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>What the C-suite receives from you</h4>
                <p>Not raw data. Your interpretation — informed by the signal, shaped by your judgment, framed as the intervention you recommend and why. Leadership never sees a number they have to decode. They see your professional reading of what is happening.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- THE WORKFLOW -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">The workflow</p>
        <h2>From signal<br /><em>to intervention.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>The work has a shape. Not a script — a shape. How you move through it will depend on your practice, your client, the specific transformation. But every Chaperone engagement passes through these six moments.</p>

          <div class="rows">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">01</div>
              <div class="row-label">Read<strong>The dashboard</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Start with the aggregate, end with the anomaly</h4>
                <p>Review the anonymised signal for the teams you are working with. Where is capacity accumulating? Where is it cycling without resolution? Which questions keep surfacing? Where is a team's participation pattern out of step with its reflective depth? The dashboard gives you a picture that no survey ever could.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">02</div>
              <div class="row-label">Interpret<strong>Form a hypothesis</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>This is where your judgment starts</h4>
                <p>The signal tells you what is happening. Your practitioner experience tells you why it might be happening and what it might mean for the transformation. This step is irreplaceable — no automation can do it, and no dashboard can substitute for it. This is the reason the Chaperone role exists.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">03</div>
              <div class="row-label">Reach<strong>Targeted human contact</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Not the individuals whose data you read — the teams that need you</h4>
                <p>Based on the hypothesis, you reach out — to the functions or cohorts showing the relevant patterns. A conversation, a workshop, a structured reflection session. The data made the timing and targeting precise. The interaction itself is entirely relational — and entirely yours.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">04</div>
              <div class="row-label">Feed back<strong>Into the aggregate</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>What you learn off-platform enriches the signal</h4>
                <p>What you hear in the human session is captured — not as individual attribution, but as contextual signal that colours the aggregate picture. The platform learns from your work. The next intervention is better calibrated because of this one.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">05</div>
              <div class="row-label">Deploy<strong>Learning modules</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>When the signal and the session both point to a capacity gap</h4>
                <p>If the pattern is trust-building, you deploy the trust module. If it is structural navigation during an M&amp;A integration, you deploy that one. Modules arrive for the right group at the moment they are metabolically ready — triggered by the data, not by a curriculum schedule.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">06</div>
              <div class="row-label">Report<strong>To leadership</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Your interpretation, their decision</h4>
                <p>You do not deliver the raw data. You deliver your professional reading: organisational readiness level, intervention indicated, expected trajectory. Leadership buys your judgment — informed by a signal layer that none of their other advisors can access.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SENIOR PARTNER REFRAME -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">Why this elevates your practice</p>
        <h2>You are the <em>senior partner.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p class="lead">AI is already hollowing out the junior layer in professional services. Interphase makes this explicit — and turns it into a value proposition for you.</p>

          <p>The grunt work of change management — data gathering, pattern recognition, report writing, synthesis — is exactly what the platform does continuously, at scale, without billing hours. What remains is exactly what you have and juniors are still developing: the capacity to hold complexity in a room, relational authority, the instinct for when to speak and when to wait, judgment shaped by having seen transformations succeed and fail in different ways.</p>

          <div class="rows">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">01</div>
              <div class="row-label">Irreplaceable<strong>What you bring</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Human presence. Interpretive judgment. Relational authority.</h4>
                <p>Knowing when to name the tension in a room and when to let it settle. Reading the emotional texture of a team. Deciding what a particular pattern means for this client, in this context, at this moment. No platform can do this. No platform should try.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">02</div>
              <div class="row-label">Automated<strong>What Interphase replaces</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>The junior layer: data gathering, pattern recognition, synthesis</h4>
                <p>Everything a junior consultant would bill hours for — done continuously, at infrastructure cost. Not instead of you. Underneath you. So your time can go to the work that only you can do.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">03</div>
              <div class="row-label">Outcome<strong>You, operating at peak value</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Freed from supervision overhead. Armed with a sharper data lens.</h4>
                <p>Your judgment becomes the product. The platform's data makes your judgment sharper than your methodology alone ever could. And your independence from the client organisation is the structural guarantee that makes all of it trustworthy in the first place.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMMERCIAL MODEL -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">What it means commercially</p>
        <h2>Certification, revenue share,<br /><em>and your network.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>Interphase is not free. The platform has real cost, the modules have real value, and your time is the most valuable thing in the arrangement. The commercial model is designed to reflect that — with you as the primary earner in every engagement.</p>

          <div class="tiles">
            <div class="tile">
              <h4>Annual certification</h4>
              <div class="big">€2,400</div>
              <p>Per year, per practitioner. Gives you access to the data lens, the dashboard, the module library, and the Interphase Chaperone community. Rigorous enough to mean something — not a rubber stamp.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <h4>Session revenue share</h4>
              <div class="big">60–70%</div>
              <p>Your share of the session fees you generate through the platform. Interphase takes 30–40% to cover the platform infrastructure, the data layer, and the module marketplace. You keep the rest.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <h4>Module deployment</h4>
              <div class="big">€500–2.5k</div>
              <p>Per module, per deployment. You earn a share each time you deploy an Interphase module — and you can contribute modules you have developed to the marketplace for other Chaperones.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="tile">
              <h4>Your network</h4>
              <div class="big">Yours</div>
              <p>The clients you bring to Interphase stay yours. The platform is an amplifier for your existing practice, not a replacement for your relationships. When you leave a client, the relationship remains with you.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>If you already have ten client relationships, Interphase gives you a sharper way to work with each one. If you have fifty, the platform scales with you. And every certified Chaperone, working well, compounds the credibility of the certification itself — which is why quality matters as much as quantity.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- HORIZON -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">The horizon</p>
        <h2>A role that <em>makes itself redundant.</em></h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p class="lead">The Chaperone model is not a permanent structural dependency for the client organisation. It is a transitional role — and this is by design.</p>

          <p>Self-Determination Theory is clear: the goal of any developmental intervention is autonomy, not perpetual dependency. A Chaperone engagement that ends with the client still needing you indefinitely has not succeeded. It has just renamed the problem. Interphase is designed around this — and your role evolves across the life of an engagement.</p>

          <div class="rows">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">P1</div>
              <div class="row-label">Entry<strong>Active Chaperone</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Heavy involvement at the start</h4>
                <p>The organisation is new to structured reflection. You read the signal closely, conduct frequent outreach, deploy modules, interpret data for leadership. High Chaperone hours, high platform value. This is the phase where trust is built and the data layer starts to compound.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">P2</div>
              <div class="row-label">Development<strong>Coaching the coaches</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Internal champions emerge</h4>
                <p>You shift from direct intervention to developing internal reflective capacity — training facilitators, consulting on signal interpretation, calibrating the Question Engine for the organisation's specific culture. You are building their muscle, not carrying it for them.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
              <div class="row-num">P3</div>
              <div class="row-label">Maturity<strong>Strategic advisor</strong></div>
              <div class="row-body">
                <h4>Largely self-sustaining</h4>
                <p>The organisation no longer needs your weekly attention. Your role becomes episodic — called in for major transformation events, providing external perspective on accumulated longitudinal data. Your relationship becomes more selective, more strategic, and more valuable per hour.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="pull">
            <blockquote>The work is not to keep being needed. The work is to build the capacity that outlasts you — and then to be trusted enough to be called back.</blockquote>
            <div class="attr">Interphase — The Chaperone principle</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- INVITATION -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-head">
        <p class="label">The invitation</p>
        <h2>If this is <em>already the work</em><br />you do.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="section-body">
        <div class="spacer"></div>
        <div class="prose">
          <p>Interphase is not trying to create a new profession. It is trying to give the practitioners who already do this work — well, and with judgment — the signal layer they have been missing their entire careers. If that is you, the platform is built for you to use.</p>

          <p>The certification programme is opening. The first Chaperones will be small in number and close to the core team, and the platform is being built in conversation with them. If you want to be part of that, we want to hear from you.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
